<title>ITALY: Italy's Bari sees June CPI at 0.0 pct mo/mo.</title>
<headline>Italy's Bari sees June CPI at 0.0 pct mo/mo.</headline>
<dateline>BARI, Italy 1997-06-20</dateline>
<text>
<p>The Italian city of Bari said its June consumer price index stood at 0.0 percent month-on-month and 0.5 percent year-on-year.</p>
<p>In May Bari's inflation rate was 0.0 percent and 0.6 percent respectively.</p>
<p>Bari is one of 11 Italian cities to publish CPI data on Friday and Monday. The city's CPI has a weighting of 5.99 percent on the national index. The 11 sample cities have a combined weighting of 75.66 percent on the total index.  </p>
<p>The following is the breakdown of the price changes.</p>
<p>(figures in brackets refer to May 1997):</p>
<p>					    Month/Month     Year/Year</p>
<p>    General index		     0.0     (0.0)   0.5    (0.6)</p>
<p>    Food				 -0.2    (-0.2)  -1.6   (-1.4)</p>
<p>    Clothing and footwear	   0.0     (0.1)   0.8    (0.9)</p>
<p>    Housing and utility charges   0.1    (-0.1)   2.2    (2.4)</p>
<p>    Furniture			   0.0    (-0.1)   0.5    (0.7)</p>
<p>    Health services		   0.2     (0.0)   2.2    (2.1)</p>
<p>    Transportation		    0.0     (0.0)   3.1    (3.5)</p>
<p>    Entertainment and culture     0.0     (0.2)  -0.9   (-0.8)</p>
<p>    Education			   0.0     (0.0)   4.0    (4.1)</p>
<p>    Hotels and restaurants	  0.0     (0.2)   0.6    (0.6)</p>
<p>    Other goods or services	 0.2     (0.3)   0.8    (0.6)</p>
